This paper deals with the logic of iterated belief revision, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (AI) and logic (LO). The paper also discusses the representation of belief states, which is a topic in multi-agent systems (MA). Additionally, the paper mentions the AGM era postulates, which are related to belief revision in computer science (CC) and cryptography (CR). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, followed by cs.LO, cs.MA, cs.CC, and cs.CR.
